The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for implementing truthful mechanisms. The use of VCG payments and analysis of pay-per-click advertising auctions suggest a connection to auction theory and market design (cs.EC). The paper also discusses the trade-off between expected quality of outcome and risk of large payments, which could involve optimization and decision making (cs.AI) as well as information theory (cs.IT).
